name: Private Character Editor File
summary: Learn about .TTE files and view a list of programs that open them.

windows.name: Open over 400 file formats with File Viewer Plus.Free Download

content: When you create custom characters, Private Character editor saves both a ".tte" file and a ".euf" file. Both are used when re-editing the character set.
NOTE: The Private Character Editor program, eudcedit.exe, is located in the C:\​Windows\​System32\​ directory.

description: Font file created by Private Character Editor, a program in Windows that allows users to make their own font characters; saves font information for a character set; can be used in conjunction with the Windows Character Map program to type custom characters.
